Total oil inventories drew by 7.8bn bbls last week. Crude stocks drew by 6.5 mln bbls, with draws in all regions. Refined product stocks drew by 1.2 mln bbls, driven by draws in the US and Singapore.

US commercial crude stocks drew by \(2.4 \text{mln}\) bbls last week. Combined with a 0.8 mln bbls build in the SPR, this gives a total crude draw of 1.6 mln bbls. Stocks at Cushing drew by \(0.8 \text{mln}\) bbls WoW. Both crude imports and exports fell WoW, declining by 0.3 and 0.6 mbpd WoW respectively. US crude production rose by \(60 \text{kb/d}\) , maintaining production levels at \(13.4 \text{mbpd}\) .

Refinery runs dropped significantly WoW, falling by 330 kbpd. This drop took refinery runs back in line with 2024 levels for the same week. PADDs 2, 3 and 5 all saw a decline in runs of \(\sim 100 \text{kbpd}\) . This was largely driven by lower refinery utilisation rates across the three regions, although the week long- outage at BP's Whiting refinery also cut PADD 2 runs. Overall US refinery utilisation rates fell by 2.0pp WoW to \(94.6\%\) .

Gasoline and distillate stocks both drew last week. Gasoline stocks drew by 1.2 mln bbls last week, a smaller draw than expected. However, the implied demand number saw a strong WoW rise, attributed to demand ahead of the Labour Day holiday. Diesel stocks drew by 1.8 mln bbls vs expectations of a small build. A strong uptick in implied diesel demand from 3.97 mbpd to \(4.14 \text{mbpd}\) helped drive the draw. US gasoline stocks are in line with the 5Y avg, while diesel stocks continue to sit near the bottom of the 5Y range.

Equal- weight (E). The stock's total return is expected to be in line with the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk- adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.

Not- Rated (NR). Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk- adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.
